content.description: Start adjacent to the tree in the middle of the face opposite of Mudmen. Using any hands you can find and a juggy rail for feet, stand up and climb up and to the right into a series of jugs.
Sit start with both hands on the sharp arete. Move up to a large gaston, and finish straight up.

Sit start near the center of the north face. Your hands are on a mini-left-facing corner. Move to good hold out left. From there, gain a series of small ledges to a slopey topout. We cleaned off a ton of muddy pine needles during the first ascent. This shares the same final moves as Bring A Brush.
content.location: It is on the main face of the boulder.

content.description: Sit start, make a few moves right on crimps, then get a left hand bump on the steep nose and a barely there right hand smear, surmount the bulge, and top out.
content.location:
This ascends the far left lip arete.  

  B45 on caltopo map

content.description: Sit start 5' to the left of Mudmen on a good rail. Move big and right to a good hold. Match and move right into the finish of Mudmen.
content.location: This is on the north face or main face.

content.description: Sit start with two so-so crimps a foot or two right of the big, upside down V-feature, and traverse right through a series of crimps and then up the headwall to a highball topout. This is a two move extension to the problem Bring Your Brush.
content.location: This roughly traverses the center of the steep wall.

content.description: Sit start with right hand on an angled crimp in the dish and a lower left hand on a flat button, and move straight up the scooped arÃªte/face.

This is a very large boulder with a lot of potential. It is camouflaged with pine needles and leaves, so it is tough to spot. It was right in front of me before I noticed it! It is all the more reason to keep exploring these woods! There are giant boulders hidden among the trees!
